Freedom Front Plus leader, Pieter Groenewald says President Cyril Ramaphosa must respond in much the same way as he did after last year's mosque attacks. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Freedom Front Plus leader Pieter Groenewald wants the President to publicly condemn farm murders. Groenewald says Cyril Ramaphosa must respond in much the same way as he did after last year's mosque attacks. WATCH: FF Plus to continue land expropriation fight “You discriminate against the young white people of South Africa, your own youth employment scheme, white people cannot participate in it because they are white,” Groenewald said. Groenewald was speaking in Parliament where opposition parties were debating the Sona. Ramaphosa is expected to respond on Wednesday. READ: Sharp increase in farm attacks since January: Afriforum AfriFrorum last year said there was a sharp increase in farm attacks during the first six months of 2018. The organisation said that  “there have been – in comparison with the first six months of 2017 – a 34 percent increase in farm attacks.”